comment.diff_hunk:
@@ -245,6 +245,13 @@ def _send_event_file_to_event_directory(self, file_path, events_folder):
             FileHelpers.deleteFile(file_path)
             print("Information: Event reporting has paused due to reaching maximum capacity in the Event directory. Reporting will resume once space is available. Events for this iteration will not be reported.")
 
+    def clear_temp_directory(self, directory_path):
+        try:
+            if os.path.exists(directory_path):
+                os.rmdir(directory_path)
comment.body: [os.rmdir](https://docs.python.org/3/library/os.html#os.rmdir) only works if the folder does not have any subfolders or files inside it - basically when it's empty. It will throw an exception. Use it if and only if you are sure that the directory is empty. Otherwise please look at something like [shutil.rmtree](https://docs.python.org/3/library/shutil.html#shutil.rmtree).

pull_request.title: Fixing missing log statements in guest agent log files by forcing dispose before process exit
pull_request.body:
Changes:
1) Calling dispose method to push the remaining logs in the event Queue, before we exit.
2) Included the entire code of  deamon method inside try catch block, to get logs before we abruptly terminate.
3) Also cleaning up of the temp folder, created to store the events initially.

pull_request.title: [enhancement] Diagnostic script to monitor system level data during a restore point operation
pull_request.body:
During snapshot operations on Linux we often come across bugs that are pretty tricky to debug without any knowledge about the system state at that point in time. This PR will introduce a small app written in go that will do exactly that.

The data this app will capture can be considered customer data - especially when strace is on - hence this app will not be shipped with normal extensions code.

The README has extensive directions on how to build and run this both manually and as part of a Restore Point operation.
